# Cursor Rules — enterprise-rag-pipeline

## Project Context
This is a production-grade multi-source RAG pipeline built with LangGraph, LangChain, NVIDIA NIM, and pgvector.
Always maintain the corrective RAG loop pattern: rewrite_query → retrieve → grade → generate → hallucination_check.

## Architecture Rules
- ALL LLM calls go through NIM endpoint (base_url from .env NIM_BASE_URL)
- ALL embeddings use NIMEmbedder from embeddings/nim_embedder.py
- State MUST flow through RAGState TypedDict defined in orchestrator/state.py
- New graph nodes go in orchestrator/nodes/ and MUST accept + return RAGState
- New ingestion sources go in ingestion/ and MUST call PGVectorStore().add_documents()

## Code Conventions
- Python 3.11+, type hints everywhere
- Pydantic v2 for all API schemas
- dotenv load_dotenv() at top of every module that reads env vars
- No hardcoded API keys, model names, or URLs — always from os.getenv()
- All nodes return full state dict: {**state, "new_key": value}

## File Structure
- orchestrator/nodes/ — one file per graph node
- ingestion/ — one file per source type (pdf, sql, web, slack)
- embeddings/ — NIM client + chunking only
- vectorstore/ — pgvector and FAISS wrappers only
- tests/ — mirror src structure, mock all external calls

## Testing
- Mock all OpenAI/NIM API calls with unittest.mock
- Mock pgvector/FAISS with in-memory fakes
- Every node must have at least one unit test in tests/

## Do Not
- Do not import from api/ into orchestrator/ or ingestion/
- Do not make real API calls in tests
- Do not commit .env — only .env.template
- Do not use sync SQLAlchemy in async FastAPI routes
